                                   A BILL

To establish a transformative justice architecture replacing punitive
incarceration with community-governed restorative processes; to provide for the
conversion of federal correctional facilities to commons resilience
infrastructure; to abolish extractive monetary assessments in federal criminal
proceedings; to establish federated community safety institutions governed under
the Ostrom Standards of Stewardship; to guarantee immediate and unconditional
Federated Commons Membership to all persons completing reparative processes; to
prohibit algorithmic risk assessment in justice determinations; to demilitarize
domestic law enforcement; and to provide for the long-term social resilience and
community sovereignty of the United States.

Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives of the United States
of America in Congress assembled,

