SECTION 4. DEFINITIONS.
================================================================================

In this Act:

(1) COMMONS MEMBER.-- The term "Commons Member" has the meaning given such term
in Section 4(4) of the Federal Resilience and Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(2) COMMUNITY SAFETY INVESTIGATOR.-- The term "Community Safety Investigator"
means a trained, non-armed community member employed by a Qualified Federated
Network pursuant to Section 302 of Title III of this Act, operating under the
governance authority of a Accountability Coordination DAO, whose function is to gather evidence
and documentation in connection with specific documented harms for the purpose
of supporting restorative justice proceedings, and who holds no authority to
arrest, detain, or use force against any person.

(3) FEDERATED COMMONS MEMBERSHIP.-- The term "Federated Commons Membership"
has the meaning given such term in Section 4(7) of the Federal Resilience and
Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(4) GUARANTEED PROVISION STANDARD.-- The term "Guaranteed Provision Standard"
has the meaning given such term in Section 4(10) of the Federal Resilience and
Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(5) HARM REPAIR AGREEMENT.-- The term "Harm Repair Agreement" means a
documented, voluntary agreement reached through a Accountability Coordination DAO proceeding
between a person who has caused harm and the person or community that
experienced harm, specifying the acts of repair, service, or material
restitution the harm-causing party agrees to undertake, the timeline for
completion, and the process by which completion is verified, and constituting
the primary instrument through which Reparative Debt is assessed and discharged
under Title II of this Act.

(6) HUMAN-IN-THE-LOOP LAYER or HITL.-- The term "Human-in-the-Loop Layer"
has the meaning given such term in Section 4(11) of the Federal Resilience and
Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(7) ACCOUNTABILITY COORDINATION DAO.-- The term "Accountability Coordination
DAO" has the meaning given such term in Section 4(13) of the Federal Resilience
and Decentralization Initiatives Act, and as further specified in Section 205 of
Title II of this Act.

(8) NATIONAL RESILIENCE LEDGER or NRL.-- The term "National Resilience Ledger"
has the meaning given such term in Section 4(14) of the Federal Resilience and
Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(9) OSTROM STANDARDS OF STEWARDSHIP.-- The term "Ostrom Standards of
Stewardship" has the meaning given such term in Section 4(16) of the Federal
Resilience and Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(10) PEACE KEEPER.-- The term "Peace Keeper" means a certified community safety
responder employed by a Qualified Federated Network pursuant to Section 301 of
Title III of this Act, trained in de-escalation, mental health crisis response,
and restorative justice facilitation, whose jurisdiction covers non-violent
incidents within the network's defined boundaries and who operates under the
governance authority of the network's Accountability Coordination DAO.

(11) PREDICTIVE POLICING SYSTEM.-- The term "Predictive Policing System" means
any software, algorithm, scoring instrument, or automated decision support tool
that uses individual or aggregate behavioral data, demographic data, geographic
data, or prior justice system contact data to generate a prediction, score, or
recommendation regarding the likelihood that a specific individual will engage
in harmful conduct in the future, or to determine the allocation of law
enforcement resources based on such predictions.

(12) QUALIFIED FEDERATED NETWORK or QFN.-- The term "Qualified Federated
Network" has the meaning given such term in Section 4(20) of the Federal
Resilience and Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(13) RECLAIMING STEWARD.-- The term "Reclaiming Steward" means, for all
purposes of this Act, an individual who is in the process of completing a Harm
Repair Agreement pursuant to Title II of this Act, or who has completed such an
agreement and thereby achieved full restoration of Commons Membership and all
associated rights and provisions. Congress finds that the punitive and
stigmatizing terminology historically applied to persons in contact with the
criminal legal system -- including "offender," "convict," "inmate," and
"prisoner" -- is inconsistent with the restorative framework established by this
Act and with the constitutional guarantees of equal protection and human dignity.
The specific conforming amendments replacing such terminology in designated
federal statutes are set forth in Section 504 of Title V of this Act.

(14) REPARATIVE DEBT.-- The term "Reparative Debt" means the obligation owed
by a person who has caused documentable harm to the person or community that
experienced that harm, assessed through the Accountability Coordination DAO process established
under Title II of this Act, denominated in Commons Credits at the Service
Resonance Rate established under Section 203 of Title II of this Act, and
dischargeable exclusively through the completion of a Harm Repair Agreement.
Reparative Debt is not a punitive fine, is not enforceable through
incarceration, and does not accrue interest.

(15) REPARATIVE JUSTICE COMMISSION.-- The term "Reparative Justice Commission"
means the body established under Section 202 of Title II of this Act to assess
historical Reparative Debt owed by governmental and institutional actors to
communities subject to systematic policy-driven harm, and to determine the
appropriate issuance of Reparative Stewardship Credits pursuant to Section 606
of the Federal Resilience and Decentralization Initiatives Act.

(16) RESILIENCE CAMPUS.-- The term "Resilience Campus" means a former federal
correctional facility converted to commons infrastructure pursuant to Title I
of this Act, governed as a Qualified Federated Cooperative under the Ostrom
Standards of Stewardship, providing housing, healthcare, cooperative education,
and transitional support to Reclaiming Stewards, and integrated into the
Federated Commons Membership network of the Qualified Federated Network within
whose geographic boundaries it operates.

(17) SERVICE RESONANCE RATE.-- The term "Service Resonance Rate" means the
standard rate, denominated in Commons Credits, at which one hour of community
service performed under a Harm Repair Agreement is credited toward the discharge
of Reparative Debt, set at a rate equivalent to one Commons Credit per hour and
adjusted periodically by the Commons Credit Governance Council established under
Section 608 of the Federal Resilience and Decentralization Initiatives Act to
maintain its relationship to the productive output of the commons economy.

(18) TRI-PARTITE COUNCIL.-- The term "Tri-Partite Council" means the governance
body established for each Resilience Campus pursuant to Section 102 of Title I
of this Act, comprising equal representation from Reclaiming Stewards resident
on the campus, members of the surrounding Qualified Federated Network community,
and cooperative enterprise representatives operating within the campus, and
constituting the primary governance institution of the campus under the Ostrom
Standards of Stewardship.

(19) ZERO-KNOWLEDGE PROOF or ZKP.-- The term "Zero-Knowledge Proof" has the
meaning given such term in Section 4(22) of the Federal Resilience and
Decentralization Initiatives Act.


